x4freetext: Pelletron
Irradiation time of about 1-2 hours was
selected according to the half-lives of the
radioisotopes produced.
Each foil was counted for 300 seconds duration
immediately after activation.  Subsequently, the foils
were recounted for successively longer duration over a
period of two weeks.
* Stacks of three self supported (about 600 mu-g/cm2)
holmium metal target foils interspersed with 2 mg/cm2
thick Al foils
* metallic holmium of thickness around 100 mu-g/cm2
vacuum evaporated onto thin (100 mu-g/cm2) aluminium
backing were used at 16O beam energy of 100 MeV.
PACE2 code
Pre-calibrated 60 cm3 HPGe detector coupled
to a 4K MCA. The efficiency of the detector as a
function of gamma ray has been determined using
standard 152Eu source. The detector resolution was
2 keV at 1332 keV.
The errors on the cross section arise mostly
from:
uncertainty in the counting statistics,
uncertainty in target thickness (5-8%),
uncertainty in detection efficiency (4%),
uncertainty in beam fluence (<5%)
uncertainty in  gamma-ray intensity
values (5-10%).
The uncertainty is created by target thickness
By CAJAD. Figure 2 contains overlapping data
points.  Therefore some inaccuracy is possible.
Last checking has been done.
